  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  All patients were recruited from the Oral Pain and Dysfunction Clinic and strictly
             satisfied the RDC-TMD criteria for .for disc displacement without reduction with
             (group IIb) or without (group IIc) limitation of mouth opening, based upon history and
             clinical examination. Additionally, pain experienced during the first examination had
             to be â‰¥ 35mm on a visual analog scale (VAS) of 100mm.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients were excluded if their medical history mentioned orofacial traumata
             (contusion or fracture), systemic disorders (e.g. rheumatoid arthritis, fibromyalgia),
             cervical disorders (operationalized as complaints, pain or referral patterns of pain
             provoked during movements of the cervical spine), neurologic disorders (e.g.
             trigeminal neuralgia, migraine or tension type headache), drug or alcohol abuse, use
             of antidepressant or hormonal medication. Participants did not receive therapy for
             symptoms of TMD within the last 2 months.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
